title: Jacqueline Jossa puts on leggy display as she sizzles in snake print dress during night on the town
text:
She is embarking on a new career venture since leaving EastEnders last year.

And Jacqueline Jossa looked nothing short of sensational as she enjoyed a night out on the town in London on Thursday.

The actress, 26, ensured all eyes were on her as she donned a snake print knee-length dress with a daring leg slit.

Stunning: Jacqueline Jossa, 28, looked nothing short of sensational as she enjoyed a night out on the town in London on Thursday

Displaying her lithe physique, Jacqueline added height to her frame with a pair of black heels and carried a matching handbag.

The EastEnders star completed her look for the evening by letting her blonde locks fall loose down her shoulders.

The TV star first made a name for herself when she was cast as Lauren Branning in the longrunning soap in 2010.

Jacqueline has set up her performing arts academy after leaving the show in 2018, following eight years as Lauren.

Style: The actress ensured all eyes were on her as she donned a snake print knee-length dress with a daring leg slit

Looking good: The EastEnders star let her blonde locks fall loose down her shoulders for the evening

The self-named academy provides classes for a pre-school age group from three to six years, middle class from five to eight years old, and a top class group from nine to 12+ years.

When Jacqueline departed her role as Lauren last year, she admitted she would be unlikely to join another soap due to her 'loyalty' to EastEnders, adding that 'I'd love to do dramas and theatre.'

The media personality has also been focusing on family life since departing the soap and is a busy mum to Mia, 14 months, eldest daughter Ella, four, as well as step-mum to husband Dan Osborne's son Teddy, five, who he shares custody of with ex Megan Tomlin.

Fashion: Displaying her lithe physique, Jacqueline added height to her frame with a pair of black heels and carried a matching handbag

Amid a series of headlines about their marriage, Jacqueline recently talked about her relationship with new! magazine, insisting her marriage is 'strong' as she added:

'We always have been. It's hard to explain it because no one would understand until you're living it.

'All I can say is that I know where I'm at and he knows where he's at. I'm still learning, he's still learning. We are very young. We are young to have three kids. It's a work in progress and nothing is perfect. We are still working on stuff.'

Jacqueline added that she goes to counselling frequently after receiving therapy while being on EastEnders, but added that she and Dan, 28, don't need couple's counselling because they're 'open with each other' and share their 'problems'.
